trend_summary: 1990s-2020 sequence shows steady suburbanisation: housing estates fill vacant interior tracts, industrial parks cluster near highway, and southern farmland shrinks. Airport keeps shape but gains extra taxiway and apron. Tree cover declines early, then rebounds via landscaped buffers and regenerated woodland.
notable_changes: Progressive build-out of new residential estates west and south of the airport
Emergence of light-industrial/warehouse blocks north-central, replacing forest patches
Runway-side modifications: extra taxiway, enlarged apron and terminal hardstand
Addition of a new arterial road improving connectivity across the centre
Marked reduction of open farmland, later replaced by managed green corridors
